# Arc: SailorArc | Scene: TheOldRoad3
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "Sarah woke up, her back hurting from the poor quality of the bedroll."
    new "Sarah woke up, her back hurting from the poor quality of the bedroll."

    old "She saw the others were also just waking up."
    new "She saw the others were also just waking up."

    old "Despite having slept through the night, Sarah felt oddly unrested."
    new "Despite having slept through the night, Sarah felt oddly unrested."

    old "No doubt it was the poor sleeping conditions, but she felt as if something else contributed to it."
    new "No doubt it was the poor sleeping conditions, but she felt as if something else contributed to it."

    old "Memories of the night before flooded her mind."
    new "Memories of the night before flooded her mind."

    old "Going with Sakar to that clearing in the forest. Staying with him as he touched himself..."
    new "Going with Sakar to that clearing in the forest. Staying with him as he touched himself..."

    old "Sarah looked at Sakar, but he didn't look back. If he was thinking about her, he wasn't letting it show."
    new "Sarah looked at Sakar, but he didn't look back. If he was thinking about her, he wasn't letting it show."

    old "She tried to rack her brain as to why she had even decided to give in to him."
    new "She tried to rack her brain as to why she had even decided to give in to him."

    old "At every turn, her revulsion seemed matched by a strange excitement."
    new "At every turn, her revulsion seemed matched by a strange excitement."

    old "She cleared her head of the memories, deciding to focus on the day."
    new "She cleared her head of the memories, deciding to focus on the day."

    old "Together, each of them began to get up and get prepared for the day ahead of them."
    new "Together, each of them began to get up and get prepared for the day ahead of them."

    old "To her own surprise, Sarah found herself now joining in their unspoken pace, doing her own part, if only small, in preparing the wagon."
    new "To her own surprise, Sarah found herself now joining in their unspoken pace, doing her own part, if only small, in preparing the wagon."

    old "Working together, they were soon ready."
    new "Working together, they were soon ready."

    old "Sigmund snapped the reins and with that, the cart pulled back into motion."
    new "Sigmund snapped the reins and with that, the cart pulled back into motion."

    old "To Sarah's delight, they did not run into any other bandits."
    new "To Sarah's delight, they did not run into any other bandits."

    old "It wasn't that she thought Sigmund and the others would not be able to handle them, but even if they did, she disliked the violence of it."
    new "It wasn't that she thought Sigmund and the others would not be able to handle them, but even if they did, she disliked the violence of it."

    old "Sigmund seemed on edge for most of their trip, even if no danger manifested itself."
    new "Sigmund seemed on edge for most of their trip, even if no danger manifested itself."

    old "With the horses in good spirits and few obstacles, they made good time."
    new "With the horses in good spirits and few obstacles, they made good time."

    old "It was under these circumstances that they came upon the one thing that broke through the monotonous environment of the forest."
    new "It was under these circumstances that they came upon the one thing that broke through the monotonous environment of the forest."

    old "Sarah saw the road part open, the forest recede on both ends, as suddenly a vast arch of stone appeared."
    new "Sarah saw the road part open, the forest recede on both ends, as suddenly a vast arch of stone appeared."

    old "She leaned over to Sigmund."
    new "She leaned over to Sigmund."

    old "He shifted around in his seat."
    new "He shifted around in his seat."

    old "That's the bridge of the three sisters."
    new "That's the bridge of the three sisters."

    old "Old. Older than maybe even these roads. The only way across the ravine."
    new "Old. Older than maybe even these roads. The only way across the ravine."

    old "She could see him scanning the road ahead."
    new "She could see him scanning the road ahead."

    old "Looks clear enough."
    new "Looks clear enough."

    old "Sarah looked out ahead as well."
    new "Sarah looked out ahead as well."

    old "Past the stone arch, a vast bridge made out of solid stone stretched further than any bridge she had ever seen in her life."
    new "Past the stone arch, a vast bridge made out of solid stone stretched further than any bridge she had ever seen in her life."

    old "Cracks ran through the construct, but despite that, it seemed solid. Like a thing that would outlast the world itself."
    new "Cracks ran through the construct, but despite that, it seemed solid. Like a thing that would outlast the world itself."

    old "The bridge had no supports, other than where it connected between one side and the other."
    new "The bridge had no supports, other than where it connected between one side and the other."

    old "Sarah wondered how such a vast construct could remain upright, but there was a lot about the bridge that seemed to challenge the rules of nature."
    new "Sarah wondered how such a vast construct could remain upright, but there was a lot about the bridge that seemed to challenge the rules of nature."

    old "As the cart slowly pulled under the arch, she could feel the air grow colder."
    new "As the cart slowly pulled under the arch, she could feel the air grow colder."

    old "The grinding of the wheels dissapeared as the smooth surface of the bridge made no noise."
    new "The grinding of the wheels dissapeared as the smooth surface of the bridge made no noise."

    old "The only thing Sarah could hear was the streaming of the water that ran far below them."
    new "The only thing Sarah could hear was the streaming of the water that ran far below them."

    old "As she turned her face to the side, she felt her mind struck by awe."
    new "As she turned her face to the side, she felt her mind struck by awe."

    old "There were no words for the sight."
    new "There were no words for the sight."

    old "Carved into the face of the mountain were three statues of women, standing side by side."
    new "Carved into the face of the mountain were three statues of women, standing side by side."

    old "What...what are they?"
    new "What...what are they?"

    old "Sigmund looked over to the enormous statues."
    new "Sigmund looked over to the enormous statues."

    old "Those are the three sisters."
    new "Those are the three sisters."

    old "But...what are they..."
    new "But...what are they..."

    old "Fuck if I know."
    new "Fuck if I know."

    old "People been asking that question for as long as I can remember."
    new "People been asking that question for as long as I can remember."

    old "Heard a hundred different stories but I don't know if a single one of em is true."
    new "Heard a hundred different stories but I don't know if a single one of em is true."

    old "All I know is they were here before even the central kingdoms were."
    new "All I know is they were here before even the central kingdoms were."

    old "Couldn't tell you who build them or why."
    new "Couldn't tell you who build them or why."

    old "Sarah tried to take in the statues, but they were so vast she struggled to look at all of them at the same time."
    new "Sarah tried to take in the statues, but they were so vast she struggled to look at all of them at the same time."

    old "Her mind seemed to revolt at the sight."
    new "Her mind seemed to revolt at the sight."

    old "Such wonders, greater than anything she'd ever seen before in her life..."
    new "Such wonders, greater than anything she'd ever seen before in her life..."

    old "Someone must have build them for a reason once."
    new "Someone must have build them for a reason once."

    old "And yet here they now stood, seemingly forgotten."
    new "And yet here they now stood, seemingly forgotten."

    old "Suddenly, Sarah felt the wagon stop."
    new "Suddenly, Sarah felt the wagon stop."

    old "Looking at Sigmund, she saw he was pulling on the reins, forcing the horses to a stop."
    new "Looking at Sigmund, she saw he was pulling on the reins, forcing the horses to a stop."

    old "Why are we stopping?"
    new "Why are we stopping?"

    old "Sigmund waved his hand, as if to dismiss her."
    new "Sigmund waved his hand, as if to dismiss her."

    old "Only for a moment. Just something I need to do."
    new "Only for a moment. Just something I need to do."

    old "Sarah watched as he leapt from the cart and walked out ahead of the cart."
    new "Sarah watched as he leapt from the cart and walked out ahead of the cart."

    old "She kept her eyes on him, following him as he continued to walk further ahead."
    new "She kept her eyes on him, following him as he continued to walk further ahead."

    old "He walked up to the edge of the bridge that looked out at the statues."
    new "He walked up to the edge of the bridge that looked out at the statues."

    old "Don't worry, he's not gonna jump."
    new "Don't worry, he's not gonna jump."

    old "Sarah was startled by Sakar's sudden appearance, but tried not to let him notice."
    new "Sarah was startled by Sakar's sudden appearance, but tried not to let him notice."

    old "I wasn't thinking that."
    new "I wasn't thinking that."

    old "But you're not curious what he's up to?"
    new "But you're not curious what he's up to?"

    old "Sarah would be lying if she said she wasn't. Part of her also hoped Sakar might know."
    new "Sarah would be lying if she said she wasn't. Part of her also hoped Sakar might know."

    old "What is he doing?"
    new "What is he doing?"

    old "He always does this."
    new "He always does this."

    old "Stops halfway on the bridge, walks over there, tosses a few coins down into the waters below."
    new "Stops halfway on the bridge, walks over there, tosses a few coins down into the waters below."

    old "Sarah turned to Sakar."
    new "Sarah turned to Sakar."

    old "Well, if I tell you I'm pretty sure he's going to run me through with his sword, so I'd rather not."
    new "Well, if I tell you I'm pretty sure he's going to run me through with his sword, so I'd rather not."

    old "Sarah frowned at him."
    new "Sarah frowned at him."

    old "So you're just gonna annoy me?"
    new "So you're just gonna annoy me?"

    old "That's the idea."
    new "That's the idea."

    old "Seriously, can't you tell me?"
    new "Seriously, can't you tell me?"

    old "Sakar suddenly looked very serious and shook his head."
    new "Sakar suddenly looked very serious and shook his head."

    old "Honestly, if you want to get the story out of him, your best bet is to get him drunk."
    new "Honestly, if you want to get the story out of him, your best bet is to get him drunk."

    old "That's just about the only time he ever talks about himself."
    new "That's just about the only time he ever talks about himself."

    old "Ooh, I think he's coming back."
    new "Ooh, I think he's coming back."

    old "Sakar dissapeared back into the cart as suddenly as he had appeared."
    new "Sakar dissapeared back into the cart as suddenly as he had appeared."

    old "A moment later, Sigmund climbed back onto the cart."
    new "A moment later, Sigmund climbed back onto the cart."

    old "Without saying a word, he grabbed the reins and snapped them, forcing the horses to move again."
    new "Without saying a word, he grabbed the reins and snapped them, forcing the horses to move again."

    old "Forget it. Just the ritual of a superstitious old fool."
    new "Forget it. Just the ritual of a superstitious old fool."

    old "Sarah wasn't sure she believed that."
    new "Sarah wasn't sure she believed that."

    old "It wasn't long after they had begun to ride again that the cart reached the other side of the bridge, pulling back onto the road."
    new "It wasn't long after they had begun to ride again that the cart reached the other side of the bridge, pulling back onto the road."

    old "The thick forests of the other side quickly faded and Sarah watched as the world around them opened up again."
    new "The thick forests of the other side quickly faded and Sarah watched as the world around them opened up again."

    old "Fields, stretching far in ever direction."
    new "Fields, stretching far in ever direction."

    old "After having been in the forest, this suddenly felt very vulernable."
    new "After having been in the forest, this suddenly felt very vulernable."

    old "We'll make camp here before nightfall. I want us well rested before we move on."
    new "We'll make camp here before nightfall. I want us well rested before we move on."

    old "As always, his instructions were dutifully followed by everyone, and before long, they had made camp and night set in."
    new "As always, his instructions were dutifully followed by everyone, and before long, they had made camp and night set in."

    old "As Sarah prepared the food and passed it around, by now having grown somewhat skilled at doing so, each member of the crew sat staring at the campfire."
    new "As Sarah prepared the food and passed it around, by now having grown somewhat skilled at doing so, each member of the crew sat staring at the campfire."

    old "Sarah saw Sakar sat close to her, closer than he otherwise would."
    new "Sarah saw Sakar sat close to her, closer than he otherwise would."

    old "She wondered if it had anything to do with the events of the night before."
    new "She wondered if it had anything to do with the events of the night before."

    old "Of course, she thought."
    new "Of course, she thought."

    old "He had made no secrets of what he wanted from her, and she'd indulged him. He would likely press her further."
    new "He had made no secrets of what he wanted from her, and she'd indulged him. He would likely press her further."

    old "Towards her other side, Sarah could see that Sigmund was pushing his food back and forth. More sullen than usual."
    new "Towards her other side, Sarah could see that Sigmund was pushing his food back and forth. More sullen than usual."

    old "She considered pushing Sigmund again on the matter of the bridge, but there was no point."
    new "She considered pushing Sigmund again on the matter of the bridge, but there was no point."

    old "He had refused to answer her before, he'd refuse to answer her now."
    new "He had refused to answer her before, he'd refuse to answer her now."

    old "Then, a thought came to her, inspired by what Sakar had told her earlier in the day."
    new "Then, a thought came to her, inspired by what Sakar had told her earlier in the day."

    old "If he was drunk enough, he might tell her."
    new "If he was drunk enough, he might tell her."

    old "Get Sigmund drunk"
    new "Get Sigmund drunk"

    old "Sarah made up her mind. She would learn more about this man, one way or another."
    new "Sarah made up her mind. She would learn more about this man, one way or another."

    old "Having made the meals multiple times, Sarah knew where the food was kept, as well as the alcohol."
    new "Having made the meals multiple times, Sarah knew where the food was kept, as well as the alcohol."

    old "Casually walking to the back of the cart, she collected a few bottles of wine."
    new "Casually walking to the back of the cart, she collected a few bottles of wine."

    old "When she came back to the campfire, she held them up excitedly."
    new "When she came back to the campfire, she held them up excitedly."

    old "Anyone care for a drink?"
    new "Anyone care for a drink?"

    old "Sakar was the first to raise his voice."
    new "Sakar was the first to raise his voice."

    old "Now we're talking!"
    new "Now we're talking!"

    old "Krip grunted approvingly."
    new "Krip grunted approvingly."

    old "I don't know if we should-"
    new "I don't know if we should-"

    old "Sakar wouldn't let Sigmun finish his sentence."
    new "Sakar wouldn't let Sigmun finish his sentence."

    old "Nah, Sigmund. We've been on the road for a good while now."
    new "Nah, Sigmund. We've been on the road for a good while now."

    old "We deserve a good break."
    new "We deserve a good break."

    old "Sarah could see a smile creep up on Sigmund's face, then he waved his hands."
    new "Sarah could see a smile creep up on Sigmund's face, then he waved his hands."

    old "Alright, just a bit then."
    new "Alright, just a bit then."

    old "Sarah eagerly began to pour out the wine for everyone."
    new "Sarah eagerly began to pour out the wine for everyone."

    old "At first she tried to think of a trick to keep the men drinking, so Sigmund would be drunk enough to loosen up."
    new "At first she tried to think of a trick to keep the men drinking, so Sigmund would be drunk enough to loosen up."

    old "But Sarah quickly learned that no such trick would be necessary."
    new "But Sarah quickly learned that no such trick would be necessary."

    old "The men drank eagerly and seemingly without restraint."
    new "The men drank eagerly and seemingly without restraint."

    old "Each glass went down faster than the next, and before long, each of them was slurring their words and wobbling back and forth."
    new "Each glass went down faster than the next, and before long, each of them was slurring their words and wobbling back and forth."

    old "Sarah herself had not been immune to the effects of the wine."
    new "Sarah herself had not been immune to the effects of the wine."

    old "Though she drank slower than the others, her smaller frame and lighter body ended up suffering nearly as much as them."
    new "Though she drank slower than the others, her smaller frame and lighter body ended up suffering nearly as much as them."

    old "But she was happy."
    new "But she was happy."

    old "The wine made her warm up and feel relaxed in a way she hadn't felt for a while."
    new "The wine made her warm up and feel relaxed in a way she hadn't felt for a while."

    old "And seeing the others laugh and be joyous was a nice change from their usual stern demeanor."
    new "And seeing the others laugh and be joyous was a nice change from their usual stern demeanor."

    old "One tall tale followed the next as each began to swap stories."
    new "One tall tale followed the next as each began to swap stories."

    old "Even Krip, usually one for few words, began to speak in sentences."
    new "Even Krip, usually one for few words, began to speak in sentences."

    old "It was like this, deep into the night and each with more than their share of wine, that Sarah finally saw her chance."
    new "It was like this, deep into the night and each with more than their share of wine, that Sarah finally saw her chance."

    old "She leaned over from her seat towards Sigmund, getting as close as she dared, and then she asked."
    new "She leaned over from her seat towards Sigmund, getting as close as she dared, and then she asked."

    old "So...Sigmund..."
    new "So...Sigmund..."

    old "He looked at her, his eyes drifting from side to side."
    new "He looked at her, his eyes drifting from side to side."

    old "On the the bridge today...what was that?"
    new "On the the bridge today...what was that?"

    old "She could see his body shift, one hand rubbing his temple."
    new "She could see his body shift, one hand rubbing his temple."

    old "Why do you pester me about it girl? Don't you have your own troubles to concern yourself with? Now you want to know mine?"
    new "Why do you pester me about it girl? Don't you have your own troubles to concern yourself with? Now you want to know mine?"

    old "Sarah could see that he was really angry. The rage almost seemed to sober him up again."
    new "Sarah could see that he was really angry. The rage almost seemed to sober him up again."

    old "Sigmund threw the empty bottle across the campsite."
    new "Sigmund threw the empty bottle across the campsite."

    old "It smashed against a rock, loudly shattering as shards of glass exploded in every direction."
    new "It smashed against a rock, loudly shattering as shards of glass exploded in every direction."

    old "Sigmund quickly stood up."
    new "Sigmund quickly stood up."

    old "You've soured my mood."
    new "You've soured my mood."

    old "I can't even drink in peace."
    new "I can't even drink in peace."

    old "He grabbed his sword and a not yet opened bottle and began to wander off down the road."
    new "He grabbed his sword and a not yet opened bottle and began to wander off down the road."

    old "Sarah had barely dared to move, but now she suddenly found herself worrying for him."
    new "Sarah had barely dared to move, but now she suddenly found herself worrying for him."

    old "She turned to Sakar."
    new "She turned to Sakar."

    old "Should...should we just let him walk off like that?"
    new "Should...should we just let him walk off like that?"

    old "Sakar shrugged and downed the last remains of a bottle."
    new "Sakar shrugged and downed the last remains of a bottle."

    old "He gets into a mood."
    new "He gets into a mood."

    old "I'm sure he'll calm down in a bit."
    new "I'm sure he'll calm down in a bit."

    old "Sakar turned to Krip."
    new "Sakar turned to Krip."

    old "Krip, can you make sure our brave captain doesn't do anything stupid?"
    new "Krip, can you make sure our brave captain doesn't do anything stupid?"

    old "Krip nodded, got up, and followed after Sigmund."
    new "Krip nodded, got up, and followed after Sigmund."

    old "Suddenly, the once so lively camp had quickly turned quiet, only the crackling of the fire could be heard."
    new "Suddenly, the once so lively camp had quickly turned quiet, only the crackling of the fire could be heard."

    old "Sarah looked at Sakar. She was angry with him."
    new "Sarah looked at Sakar. She was angry with him."

    old "You said he would tell me if he was drunk!"
    new "You said he would tell me if he was drunk!"

    old "Don't go trying to blame me."
    new "Don't go trying to blame me."

    old "I never told you to try and play any games with him."
    new "I never told you to try and play any games with him."

    old "Sarah grew even more annoyed."
    new "Sarah grew even more annoyed."

    old "Now he hates me!"
    new "Now he hates me!"

    old "He doesn't hate you, Sarah. He's just blowing off some steam. It's a touchy subject, and he doesn't like to talk about it."
    new "He doesn't hate you, Sarah. He's just blowing off some steam. It's a touchy subject, and he doesn't like to talk about it."

    old "You should really learn to keep your nose out other people's business."
    new "You should really learn to keep your nose out other people's business."

    old "It's bad manners in general, and out here on the road it's dangerous too."
    new "It's bad manners in general, and out here on the road it's dangerous too."

    old "Sarah suddenly stood up."
    new "Sarah suddenly stood up."

    old "I don't need you to lecture me about manners!"
    new "I don't need you to lecture me about manners!"

    old "She watched Sakar lean back, casually, continuing to drink as though she'd said nothing that even meritted a response."
    new "She watched Sakar lean back, casually, continuing to drink as though she'd said nothing that even meritted a response."

    old "Still angry, but with nowhere to go, Sarah sat back down at the campfire."
    new "Still angry, but with nowhere to go, Sarah sat back down at the campfire."

    old "From the corner of her eyes, she could see Sakar glancing over to her."
    new "From the corner of her eyes, she could see Sakar glancing over to her."

    old "Wanna go for a walk?"
    new "Wanna go for a walk?"

    old "Sarah knew that was likely the least of his intentions."
    new "Sarah knew that was likely the least of his intentions."

    old "Sure, clear my head"
    new "Sure, clear my head"

    old "Still, Sarah wanted to clear her head."
    new "Still, Sarah wanted to clear her head."

    old "The business with Sigmund was still haunting her, and she wanted to get away from it. Maybe a walk would do the trick."
    new "The business with Sigmund was still haunting her, and she wanted to get away from it. Maybe a walk would do the trick."

    old "She stood up together with Sakar and began to follow him."
    new "She stood up together with Sakar and began to follow him."

    old "They took off down the road, the opposite direction of where Sigmund had gone."
    new "They took off down the road, the opposite direction of where Sigmund had gone."

    old "It wasn't long before they were far enough from the camp that darkness began to encroach on them from every direction."
    new "It wasn't long before they were far enough from the camp that darkness began to encroach on them from every direction."

    old "Sarah still felt some resentment to Sakar."
    new "Sarah still felt some resentment to Sakar."

    old "You know, it's your fault."
    new "You know, it's your fault."

    old "Is it now?"
    new "Is it now?"

    old "You gave me the idea...to get him drunk..."
    new "You gave me the idea...to get him drunk..."

    old "I'll take a fraction of the blame for giving you the idea."
    new "I'll take a fraction of the blame for giving you the idea."

    old "But what kind of a fool acts on one of my ideas?"
    new "But what kind of a fool acts on one of my ideas?"

    old "Sarah had to laugh."
    new "Sarah had to laugh."

    old "Yeah, I guess you're right. Trusting your idea says a lot about me."
    new "Yeah, I guess you're right. Trusting your idea says a lot about me."

    old "As they walked further from the camp, leaving its warm fire behind, the air quickly grew colder all around."
    new "As they walked further from the camp, leaving its warm fire behind, the air quickly grew colder all around."

    old "To her surprise, she noticed Sakar undoing his jacket."
    new "To her surprise, she noticed Sakar undoing his jacket."

    old "He handed it to her."
    new "He handed it to her."

    old "She knew the proper response was to refuse him, allow him to offer it again, but she was too eager for warmth."
    new "She knew the proper response was to refuse him, allow him to offer it again, but she was too eager for warmth."

    old "Sarah took the jacket from him."
    new "Sarah took the jacket from him."

    old "Ooh, it's no bother. I'm too warm anyway."
    new "Ooh, it's no bother. I'm too warm anyway."

    old "She could see that this wasn't true, but she appreciated him for pretending."
    new "She could see that this wasn't true, but she appreciated him for pretending."

    old "They walked further along the road."
    new "They walked further along the road."

    old "You know his story though, right?"
    new "You know his story though, right?"

    old "Sakar looked at her. For the first time, she could see something new in his face."
    new "Sakar looked at her. For the first time, she could see something new in his face."

    old "Hesitant. Something was holding him back."
    new "Hesitant. Something was holding him back."

    old "Well...I do. But I'm not so sure if it's my place to tell you."
    new "Well...I do. But I'm not so sure if it's my place to tell you."

    old "Please, I'll do anything"
    new "Please, I'll do anything"

    old "Sarah grabbed Sakar by his wrist, forcing him to stop."
    new "Sarah grabbed Sakar by his wrist, forcing him to stop."

    old "She looked deep into his eyes."
    new "She looked deep into his eyes."

    old "The alcohol had given her a courage and a boldness that was strange to her."
    new "The alcohol had given her a courage and a boldness that was strange to her."

    old "Please, tell me. I'll do...anything."
    new "Please, tell me. I'll do...anything."

    old "Sarah put the emphasis on the word, knowing Sakar would understand her well enough."
    new "Sarah put the emphasis on the word, knowing Sakar would understand her well enough."

    old "His smile and perfect white teeth cut through the darkness."
    new "His smile and perfect white teeth cut through the darkness."

    old "Anything, is it?"
    new "Anything, is it?"

    old "She could feel her face begin to burn."
    new "She could feel her face begin to burn."

    old "Sarah knew she hadn't been raised like this. To be forward."
    new "Sarah knew she hadn't been raised like this. To be forward."

    old "But what did it matter."
    new "But what did it matter."

    old "She was out here, countless miles away from civilization. Her home country, and anyone she might have owed any allegiance, was in ashes."
    new "She was out here, countless miles away from civilization. Her home country, and anyone she might have owed any allegiance, was in ashes."

    old "The old rules didn't apply anymore."
    new "The old rules didn't apply anymore."

    old "Yes...anything."
    new "Yes...anything."

    old "She watched as Sakar rubbed the back of his head, seemingly still in doubt."
    new "She watched as Sakar rubbed the back of his head, seemingly still in doubt."

    old "I mean..."
    new "I mean..."

    old "Fuck you for getting me into trouble. But fuck me if I'm gonna pass on this."
    new "Fuck you for getting me into trouble. But fuck me if I'm gonna pass on this."

    old "Suddenly, Sarah felt him grab her wrist."
    new "Suddenly, Sarah felt him grab her wrist."

